senses.sense_definition: Any of the values that divide a sorted data set into seven equal parts.

examples.text: The researcher analyzed the income distribution by calculating each <w>septile</w>.
Students in the top <w>septile</w> were eligible for the advanced mathematics program.

senses.sense_definition: An astrological aspect of approximately 51.5 degrees, representing one-seventh of a circle.

examples.text: The astrologer interpreted the <w>septile</w> between the two planets as a sign of destiny.
A <w>septile</w> is considered a minor aspect in most traditional horoscopes.
The surgeon examined the <w>septile</w> tissue for any signs of damage.
Microscopic analysis revealed a defect in the <w>septile</w> wall of the structure.
